  <h2>The Budget Drivers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Soil and site evaluation.</strong> What the ground allows shapes the system that can be installed.</li>
    <li><strong>System type and design.</strong> Conventional and alternative systems involve different work.</li>
    <li><strong>Access and layout.</strong> Equipment access, slope and distance affect the project.</li>
    <li><strong>Approvals and restoration.</strong> Applicable approvals and putting the property back together both matter.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Planning Comes First</h2>
  <p>
    Budgets firm up after the site is evaluated and a design is chosen — see the <a href="/resources/septic-installation-replacement/">installation and replacement hub</a> for how these projects generally proceed. To begin, <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a> with your property details.
  </p>

